Fill and boil your #kettle{} for the pasta.

Turn your #grill{} on to high.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}(halved).

Halve the @lemon{1}(halved).

Pick the @tarragon{1}(leaves picked and roughly chopped) from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on a medium high heat.

When hot, add the halved tomatoes and cook, stirring frequently until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @sea bass fillets{2} on a lightly oiled #baking tray{} skin-side up, drizzle on @olive oil{1%tsp} and season with @salt{}, grill on the top shelf until cooked through and the skin is crispy, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Once the tomatoes have softened, add the @creme fraiche{150%g}, tarragon, @vegetable stock powder{1} and @water{50%ml} to the pan.

Bring to the boil, turn the heat down and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

In the meantime, pour the boiling water into a #saucepan{} on high heat. Add the @fresh tagliatelle{200%g} and @salt{0.5%tsp} and simmer until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Drain in a #colander{} and pop into the pan with the creamy sauce. Season the sauce to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pop the @pea shoots{40} into a #small bowl{} with half the lemon juice, a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Mix to dress.

Share the pasta between your bowls.

Top with the seabass and serve the salad along side. Enjoy!